snippet.textDisplay:
Demi.
I know that you already have over 21K comments on this video, and will probably never read mine, which I can't blame you for.
You're busy, you have a life, and I'm just a fan commenting on one of your videos.
But, in the slim chance that you do read this, I just wanted to tell you something.

Confident is a song I listen to when I need that boost. It's what I listen to when the world has got me down.
Stone Cold is a song I listen to when I need to know, I'm not the only one who feels that way.
Father is a song I listen to when I need to remember to forgive, not just my dad, but other people in my life.
Heart Attack is a song I listen to when I can't describe how He makes me feel.
These are just a few.
My point is, I know it doesn't always feel like it, and I know that having fans isn't exactly the same as having friends. But we are listening.
And, the people who are pestering you, asking where you are and what happened, need to stop. Yes, you are famous, but you're still human.
I don't mean that in a bad way, more of a reassuring way.
You are so strong, Demi. You've been through SO much, and you have a tough job. It's okay to crack.
The important thing is not to let it get to you. Remember that you are SO much more than your mistakes. Demi, I'm a crazy hardcore fan, but I respect you as a person.
Don't release your music until You are ready.
Don't perform until You are ready.
I don't know what's going on, but based on this song, something is going on.
Your true Lovatics will understand, and we'll wait. We love you and your music, but your health, mental and physical, is more important.
Keep doing what you're doing, just in your own time.


If you ever read this, I hope it was worth the time that it took.
Thank You, Demi Lovato.
You've been there for us, now it's our turn to be there for you.

snippet.textDisplay: Im a guy but I can relate to this. I recently published my 1st book, had somewhat of "internet fame" (note the " . ") But my life is falling apart & I am battling a deep depression. I tried killing myself but after 26hrs in a coma I came back. Still I find no joy in being here. I feel like I dont belong here. I write almost daily but I stopped posting my work. Stopped promoting my book and just try to sleep my days and nights away. People say "oh just get up, others have it worse, be grateful" But until you battle this demon called major depression disorder you cant understand just how hard it is for us to find strength or better yet, WORTH in our lives to carry on. I wish I could give Demi a big hug and tell her she is not alone and we are listening. 💔

snippet.textDisplay: Jesus is always listening to every word, Jesus is there for you in the dark times and the good times. Jesus is the Son of God and he listens to every prayer, Jesus will change your heart. Jesus is coming back, repent and always stay strong in the Lord because Jesus has overcome all things. Through faith alone in Christ alone, we will experience the promise of eternal life if we’d just trust Jesus and let him into our daily lives to work on our hearts. Jesus died for you, was buried for you, and was raised from his own death on the third day to sit at the right hand of God. Jesus is alive, and he’s coming back. Jesus loves you so much, trust Jesus with every small detail of your life and he will lead and guide you to something so much greater than you could possibly imagine. The Kingdom that Jesus has prepared for those who trust in him is the most beautiful. Jesus is coming back to establish his Kingdom on Earth just as it is in Heaven. We all must repent of our sins, we are all sinners who need the forgiveness and grace of Jesus Christ. May the grace of the Lord be with all God’s people, Amen.
